{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":3005,"text":"I thought if I skipped it might help my nerves,"},{"time":6227,"text":"but I'm actually having a paradoxical reaction to that,"},{"time":9413,"text":"so that was a bad idea. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11235,"text":"Anyway, I was really delighted to receive the invitation"},{"time":14656,"text":"to present to you some of my music and some of my work"},{"time":18593,"text":"as a composer, presumably because it appeals"},{"time":21687,"text":"to my well-known and abundant narcissism. (Laughter)"},{"time":25670,"text":"And I'm not kidding, I just think we should just"},{"time":28278,"text":"say that and move forward. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":31734,"text":"So, but the thing is, a dilemma quickly arose,"},{"time":34614,"text":"and that is that I'm really bored with music,"},{"time":36819,"text":"and I'm really bored with the role of the composer,"},{"time":39885,"text":"and so I decided to put that idea, boredom,"},{"time":43093,"text":"as the focus of my presentation to you today."},{"time":46067,"text":"And I'm going to share my music with you, but I hope"},{"time":48355,"text":"that I'm going to do so in a way that tells a story,"},{"time":50590,"text":"tells a story about how I used boredom as a catalyst"},{"time":53999,"text":"for creativity and invention, and how boredom"},{"time":56553,"text":"actually forced me to change the fundamental question"},{"time":59714,"text":"that I was asking in my discipline,"},{"time":61795,"text":"and how boredom also, in a sense,"},{"time":63854,"text":"pushed me towards taking on roles beyond the sort of"},{"time":68298,"text":"most traditional, narrow definition of a composer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70908,"text":"What I'd like to do today is to start with an excerpt"},{"time":73379,"text":"of a piece of music at the piano."},{"time":76207,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":85522,"text":"Okay, I wrote that. (Laughter)"},{"time":88836,"text":"No, it's not — (Applause) Oh, why thank you."},{"time":90743,"text":"No, no, I didn't write that."},{"time":92374,"text":"In fact, that was a piece by Beethoven,"},{"time":94646,"text":"and so I was not functioning as a composer."},{"time":97201,"text":"Just now I was functioning in the role of the interpreter,"},{"time":100252,"text":"and there I am, interpreter."},{"time":102313,"text":"So, an interpreter of what? Of a piece of music, right?"},{"time":105022,"text":"But we can ask the question, \"But is it music?\""},{"time":109229,"text":"And I say this rhetorically, because of course"},{"time":111009,"text":"by just about any standard we would have to concede"},{"time":113830,"text":"that this is, of course, a piece of music,"},{"time":115778,"text":"but I put this here now because,"},{"time":118104,"text":"just to set it in your brains for the moment,"},{"time":120387,"text":"because we're going to return to this question."},{"time":122228,"text":"It's going to be a kind of a refrain"},{"time":124010,"text":"as we go through the presentation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125821,"text":"So here we have this piece of music by Beethoven,"},{"time":128049,"text":"and my problem with it is, it's boring."},{"time":131255,"text":"I mean, you — I'm just like, a hush, huh -- It's like -- (Laughter)"},{"time":138075,"text":"It's Beethoven, how can you say that?"},{"time":139793,"text":"No, well, I don't know, it's very familiar to me."},{"time":141528,"text":"I had to practice it as a kid, and I'm really sick of it. So -- (Laughter)"},{"time":144559,"text":"I would, so what I might like to try to do is to change it,"},{"time":147282,"text":"to transform it in some ways, to personalize it,"},{"time":149926,"text":"so I might take the opening, like this idea --"},{"time":152353,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":154561,"text":"and then I might substitute -- (Music)"},{"time":159458,"text":"and then I might improvise on that melody"},{"time":161097,"text":"that goes forward from there -- (Music)"},{"time":164732,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":190754,"text":"So that might be the kind of thing -- Why thank you."},{"time":193866,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":197461,"text":"That would be the kind of thing that I would do,"},{"time":199579,"text":"and it's not necessarily better than the Beethoven."},{"time":201676,"text":"In fact, I think it's not better than it. The thing is -- (Laughter) --"},{"time":205408,"text":"it's more interesting to me. It's less boring for me."},{"time":210707,"text":"I'm really leaning into me, because I, because I have"},{"time":213877,"text":"to think about what decisions I'm going to make on the fly"},{"time":217449,"text":"as that Beethoven text is running in time through my head"},{"time":220651,"text":"and I'm trying to figure out what kinds of transformations"},{"time":222856,"text":"I'm going to make to it."},{"time":224454,"text":"So this is an engaging enterprise for me, and"},{"time":227029,"text":"I've really leaned into that first person pronoun thing there,"},{"time":231687,"text":"and now my face appears twice, so I think we can agree"},{"time":234008,"text":"that this is a fundamentally solipsistic enterprise. (Laughter)"},{"time":237699,"text":"But it's an engaging one, and it's interesting to me"},{"time":240113,"text":"for a while, but then I get bored with it, and by it,"},{"time":242533,"text":"I actually mean, the piano, because it becomes,"},{"time":245184,"text":"it's this familiar instrument, it's timbral range is actually"},{"time":248402,"text":"pretty compressed, at least when you play on the keyboard,"},{"time":250923,"text":"and if you're not doing things like listening to it"},{"time":253533,"text":"after you've lit it on fire or something like that, you know."},{"time":256256,"text":"It gets a little bit boring, and so pretty soon"},{"time":258225,"text":"I go through other instruments, they become familiar,"},{"time":260385,"text":"and eventually I find myself designing and constructing"},{"time":263062,"text":"my own instrument, and I brought one with me today,"},{"time":267225,"text":"and I thought I would play a little bit on it for you"},{"time":270161,"text":"so you can hear what it sounds like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272367,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":283780,"text":"You gotta have doorstops, that's important. (Laughter)"},{"time":289543,"text":"I've got combs. They're the only combs that I own. (Music)"},{"time":292651,"text":"They're all mounted on my instruments. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":295807,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":304866,"text":"I can actually do all sorts of things. I can play"},{"time":307451,"text":"with a violin bow. I don't have to use the chopsticks."},{"time":309949,"text":"So we have this sound. (Music)"},{"time":317802,"text":"And with a bank of live electronics,"},{"time":319846,"text":"I can change the sounds radically. (Music)"},{"time":323967,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":333041,"text":"Like that, and like this. (Music)"},{"time":339292,"text":"And so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341410,"text":"So this gives you a little bit of an idea of the sound world"},{"time":343549,"text":"of this instrument, which I think is quite interesting"},{"time":346226,"text":"and it puts me in the role of the inventor, and the nice thing about —"},{"time":350000,"text":"This instrument is called the Mouseketeer ... (Laughter)"},{"time":353119,"text":"and the cool thing about it is"},{"time":355383,"text":"I'm the world's greatest Mouseketeer player. (Laughter)"},{"time":358951,"text":"Okay? (Applause)"},{"time":360570,"text":"So in that regard, this is one of the things,"},{"time":363746,"text":"this is one of the privileges of being,"},{"time":365606,"text":"and here's another role, the inventor, and by the way,"},{"time":368612,"text":"when I told you that I'm the world's greatest,"},{"time":370790,"text":"if you're keeping score, we've had narcissism and solipsism"},{"time":374794,"text":"and now a healthy dose of egocentricism."},{"time":376798,"text":"I know some of you are just, you know, bingo! Or, I don't know. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":380398,"text":"Anyway, so this is also a really enjoyable role."},{"time":385945,"text":"I should concede also that I'm the world's worst Mouseketeer player,"},{"time":388677,"text":"and it was this distinction that I was most worried about"},{"time":390927,"text":"when I was on that prior side of the tenure divide."},{"time":393864,"text":"I'm glad I'm past that. We're not going to go into that."},{"time":396350,"text":"I'm crying on the inside. There are still scars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399307,"text":"Anyway, but I guess my point is that all of these enterprises"},{"time":403123,"text":"are engaging to me in their multiplicity, but as I've presented them"},{"time":406858,"text":"to you today, they're actually solitary enterprises,"},{"time":410210,"text":"and so pretty soon I want to commune with other people, and so"},{"time":413237,"text":"I'm delighted that in fact I get to compose works for them."},{"time":415755,"text":"I get to write, sometimes for soloists and I get to work with one person,"},{"time":418841,"text":"sometimes full orchestras, and I work with a lot of people,"},{"time":422150,"text":"and this is probably the capacity, the role creatively"},{"time":425829,"text":"for which I'm probably best known professionally."},{"time":428991,"text":"Now, some of my scores as a composer look like this,"},{"time":431966,"text":"and others look like this,"},{"time":434039,"text":"and some look like this,"},{"time":436123,"text":"and I make all of these by hand, and it's really tedious."},{"time":439169,"text":"It takes a long, long time to make these scores,"},{"time":441502,"text":"and right now I'm working on a piece"},{"time":443675,"text":"that's 180 pages in length,"},{"time":445698,"text":"and it's just a big chunk of my life, and I'm just pulling out hair."},{"time":449894,"text":"I have a lot of it, and that's a good thing I suppose. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":452403,"text":"So this gets really boring and really tiresome for me,"},{"time":455967,"text":"so after a while the process of notating is not only boring,"},{"time":458940,"text":"but I actually want the notation to be more interesting,"},{"time":462072,"text":"and so that's pushed me to do other projects like this one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464791,"text":"This is an excerpt from a score called"},{"time":467021,"text":"\"The Metaphysics of Notation.\""},{"time":469212,"text":"The full score is 72 feet wide."},{"time":471756,"text":"It's a bunch of crazy pictographic notation."},{"time":474454,"text":"Let's zoom in on one section of it right here. You can see"},{"time":477340,"text":"it's rather detailed. I do all of this with drafting templates,"},{"time":481157,"text":"with straight edges, with French curves, and by freehand,"},{"time":484774,"text":"and the 72 feet was actually split"},{"time":487428,"text":"into 12 six-foot-wide panels that were installed"},{"time":490463,"text":"around the Cantor Arts Center Museum lobby balcony,"},{"time":495347,"text":"and it appeared for one year in the museum,"},{"time":499155,"text":"and during that year, it was experienced as visual art"},{"time":502013,"text":"most of the week, except, as you can see in these pictures,"},{"time":503914,"text":"on Fridays, from noon til one, and only during that time,"},{"time":506952,"text":"various performers came and interpreted these strange"},{"time":510332,"text":"and undefined pictographic glyphs. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":513611,"text":"Now this was a really exciting experience for me."},{"time":517295,"text":"It was gratifying musically, but I think"},{"time":518898,"text":"the more important thing is it was exciting because I got to take on"},{"time":521594,"text":"another role, especially given that it appeared in a museum,"},{"time":524490,"text":"and that is as visual artist. (Laughter)"},{"time":527766,"text":"We're going to fill up the whole thing, don't worry. (Laughter)"},{"time":530266,"text":"I am multitudes. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532269,"text":"So one of the things is that, I mean, some people"},{"time":535173,"text":"would say, like, \"Oh, you're being a dilettante,\""},{"time":536960,"text":"and maybe that's true. I can understand how, I mean,"},{"time":539537,"text":"because I don't have a pedigree in visual art"},{"time":541696,"text":"and I don't have any training, but it's just something"},{"time":543732,"text":"that I wanted to do as an extension of my composition,"},{"time":546199,"text":"as an extension of a kind of creative impulse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549099,"text":"I can understand the question, though. \"But is it music?\""},{"time":552195,"text":"I mean, there's not any traditional notation."},{"time":554454,"text":"I can also understand that sort of implicit criticism"},{"time":556707,"text":"in this piece, \"S-tog,\" which I made when I was living in Copenhagen."},{"time":560079,"text":"I took the Copenhagen subway map and"},{"time":562066,"text":"I renamed all the stations to abstract musical provocations,"},{"time":565198,"text":"and the players, who are synchronized with stopwatches,"},{"time":567969,"text":"follow the timetables, which are listed in minutes past the hour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570830,"text":"So this is a case of actually adapting something,"},{"time":573891,"text":"or maybe stealing something,"},{"time":575774,"text":"and then turning it into a musical notation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578115,"text":"Another adaptation would be this piece."},{"time":580270,"text":"I took the idea of the wristwatch, and I turned it into a musical score."},{"time":583616,"text":"I made my own faces, and had a company fabricate them,"},{"time":586854,"text":"and the players follow these scores."},{"time":589092,"text":"They follow the second hands, and as they pass over"},{"time":591113,"text":"the various symbols, the players respond musically."},{"time":594099,"text":"Here's another example from another piece,"},{"time":596322,"text":"and then its realization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598376,"text":"So in these two capacities, I've been scavenger,"},{"time":600855,"text":"in the sense of taking, like, the subway map, right,"},{"time":603242,"text":"or thief maybe, and I've also been designer,"},{"time":605760,"text":"in the case of making the wristwatches."},{"time":608075,"text":"And once again, this is, for me, interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611655,"text":"Another role that I like to take on is that of the performance artist."},{"time":614974,"text":"Some of my pieces have these kind of weird theatric elements,"},{"time":617661,"text":"and I often perform them. I want to show you a clip"},{"time":619815,"text":"from a piece called \"Echolalia.\""},{"time":621579,"text":"This is actually being performed by Brian McWhorter,"},{"time":624650,"text":"who is an extraordinary performer."},{"time":625955,"text":"Let's watch a little bit of this, and please notice the instrumentation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629387,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":658275,"text":"Okay, I hear you were laughing nervously because"},{"time":659959,"text":"you too could hear that the drill was a little bit sharp,"},{"time":662253,"text":"the intonation was a little questionable. (Laughter)"},{"time":664381,"text":"Let's watch just another clip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666393,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":676969,"text":"You can see the mayhem continues, and there's, you know,"},{"time":679665,"text":"there were no clarinets and trumpets"},{"time":681543,"text":"and flutes and violins. Here's a piece that has"},{"time":683447,"text":"an even more unusual, more peculiar instrumentation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686002,"text":"This is \"Tlön,\" for three conductors and no players. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":702327,"text":"This was based on the experience of actually watching"},{"time":704267,"text":"two people having a virulent argument in sign language,"},{"time":706783,"text":"which produced no decibels to speak of,"},{"time":708642,"text":"but affectively, psychologically, was a very loud experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712053,"text":"So, yeah, I get it, with, like, the weird appliances"},{"time":715721,"text":"and then the total absence of conventional instruments"},{"time":719823,"text":"and this glut of conductors, people might, you know,"},{"time":722696,"text":"wonder, yeah, \"Is this music?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":725599,"text":"But let's move on to a piece where clearly I'm behaving myself,"},{"time":729446,"text":"and that is my \"Concerto for Orchestra.\""},{"time":731933,"text":"You're going to notice a lot of conventional instruments"},{"time":733931,"text":"in this clip. (Music)"},{"time":737631,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":750478,"text":"This, in fact, is not the title of this piece."},{"time":752518,"text":"I was a bit mischievous. In fact, to make it more interesting,"},{"time":755073,"text":"I put a space right in here, and this is the actual title of the piece."},{"time":759358,"text":"Let's continue with that same excerpt."},{"time":761384,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":771677,"text":"It's better with a florist, right? (Laughter) (Music)"},{"time":779767,"text":"Or at least it's less boring. Let's watch a couple more clips."},{"time":782003,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":795979,"text":"So with all these theatric elements, this pushes me in another role,"},{"time":799027,"text":"and that would be, possibly, the dramaturge."},{"time":801850,"text":"I was playing nice. I had to write the orchestra bits, right?"},{"time":806337,"text":"Okay? But then there was this other stuff, right?"},{"time":808800,"text":"There was the florist, and I can understand that,"},{"time":810733,"text":"once again, we're putting pressure on the ontology of music"},{"time":813873,"text":"as we know it conventionally,"},{"time":816586,"text":"but let's look at one last piece today I'm going to share with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821009,"text":"This is going to be a piece called \"Aphasia,\""},{"time":823674,"text":"and it's for hand gestures synchronized to sound,"},{"time":827109,"text":"and this invites yet another role, and final one"},{"time":829848,"text":"I'll share with you, which is that of the choreographer."},{"time":832421,"text":"And the score for the piece looks like this,"},{"time":834899,"text":"and it instructs me, the performer, to make"},{"time":839309,"text":"various hand gestures at very specific times"},{"time":842039,"text":"synchronized with an audio tape, and that audio tape"},{"time":844293,"text":"is made up exclusively of vocal samples."},{"time":847170,"text":"I recorded an awesome singer,"},{"time":849592,"text":"and I took the sound of his voice in my computer,"},{"time":851937,"text":"and I warped it in countless ways to come up with"},{"time":854536,"text":"the soundtrack that you're about to hear."},{"time":856804,"text":"And I'll perform just an excerpt of \"Aphasia\" for you here. Okay?"},{"time":861769,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":900108,"text":"So that gives you a little taste of that piece. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":906731,"text":"Yeah, okay, that's kind of weird stuff."},{"time":909015,"text":"Is it music? Here's how I want to conclude."},{"time":911254,"text":"I've decided, ultimately, that this is the wrong question,"},{"time":913830,"text":"that this is not the important question."},{"time":915788,"text":"The important question is, \"Is it interesting?\""},{"time":918521,"text":"And I follow this question, not worrying about \"Is it music?\" --"},{"time":921413,"text":"not worrying about the definition of the thing that I'm making."},{"time":923899,"text":"I allow my creativity to push me"},{"time":926352,"text":"in directions that are simply interesting to me,"},{"time":928512,"text":"and I don't worry about the likeness of the result"},{"time":931561,"text":"to some notion, some paradigm,"},{"time":933617,"text":"of what music composition is supposed to be,"},{"time":936606,"text":"and that has actually urged me, in a sense,"},{"time":939049,"text":"to take on a whole bunch of different roles,"},{"time":940784,"text":"and so what I want you to think about is,"},{"time":942919,"text":"to what extent might you change the fundamental question"},{"time":946137,"text":"in your discipline, and, okay,"},{"time":948860,"text":"I'm going to put one extra little footnote in here,"},{"time":951240,"text":"because, like, I realized I mentioned"},{"time":952854,"text":"some psychological defects earlier, and we also,"},{"time":955789,"text":"along the way, had a fair amount of obsessive behavior,"},{"time":959532,"text":"and there was some delusional behavior and things like that,"},{"time":961693,"text":"and here I think we could say that this is an argument"},{"time":964674,"text":"for self-loathing and a kind of schizophrenia,"},{"time":966653,"text":"at least in the popular use of the term,"},{"time":968589,"text":"and I really mean dissociative identity disorder, okay. (Laughter)"},{"time":970823,"text":"Anyway, despite those perils, I would urge you"},{"time":973886,"text":"to think about the possibility that you might take on roles"},{"time":976461,"text":"in your own work, whether they are neighboring"},{"time":978552,"text":"or far-flung from your professional definition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":981050,"text":"And with that, I thank you very much. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":982827,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}